#nav-search.doc-content 
    h1 insertSearch();
    .definition  Insert a quick find enabling to search within the item descriptors in a defined or all workspaces.
        br
        |This function gets included in all pages automatically and is defined in 
        span.path /public/javascripts/contents/nav.js
        |. 
        br
        |Styling of the given contents is defined in 
        span.path /public/stylesheets/contents/nav.css 
        | based on the primary class search-list.
        img(src='images/docs/nav-search-1.png' style='display:block;margin-top:20px;height:355px;')
    h2 DOM Elements 
    p Insert the following base element to your pug file to add the workspace views in your page:
    p.code #search 
    p You can also use another id, but you will then have to pass the right name using the 'id' parameter (see section Parameters). Add the following optional classes to this DOM element to adjust the contents display:
    p 
        table.row-hovering 
            tr 
                th Class Name 
                th Description
            tr 
                td surface-level-[1..5]
                td Add the UI classes surface-level-1 through surface-level-5 to adjust the background color of the search element 

    h2 Parameters
    p Various parameters can be provided when using insertSearch. All parameters listed below are optional and can be passed using a JSON object. See this example call: 
    p.code insertSearch('208', { 'workspace' : '57', 'limit' : 100 });
    p   
        table.parameters.row-hovering 
            tr 
                th.nowrap Parameter 
                th Description
                th Type 
                th Required 
                th Default 
            tr 
                td id 
                td ID of the DOM element where the search panel should be inserted
                td String
                td No
                td search
            tr 
                td header 
                td Can be used to suppress addition of the panel header element
                td Boolean
                td No
                td false
            tr 
                td headerLabel
                td Sets the header label (if header is enabled)
                td String
                td No
                td Search
            tr 
                td headerToggle 
                td Enables collapsing and expanding the panel
                td Boolean
                td No 
                td false
            tr 
                td placeholder 
                td Sets the placeholder text for the search input element
                td String
                td No 
                td 'Enter search critieria'
            tr 
                td buttonLabel 
                td Sets the label of the button to run the search (users can also press the enter key to run the given search)
                td String
                td No 
                td 'Submit'
            tr 
                td reset 
                td Enables a reset button for the search panel
                td Boolean
                td No
                td true
            tr 
                td tileCounter 
                td A counter can be displayed in each tile instead of an icon to let users remember given search results easieer
                td Boolean
                td No
                td false
            tr 
                td icon 
                td Sets the icon to be displayed for each tile (this setting gets overwritten with the previous parameter tileCounter)
                td String
                td No
                td 'icon-checkmark'
            tr 
                td images 
                td Set this parameter to true if the first image of each result should be displayed within the tile
                td Boolean
                td No
                td false
            tr 
                td size 
                td Set the size of tiles (xxs, xs, s, m, l, xl or xxl)
                td String
                td No
                td 'm'
            tr 
                td limit 
                td Set maximum limit of search results (if more search results would be available, a given text message will be shown below the list of search results)
                td Integer
                td No 
                td 50
            tr 
                td workspace 
                td Provide a workspac ID to restrict the search for the given workspace
                td String
                td No 
                td ''
            tr 
                td baseQuery 
                td Provide a base query string which will be added to the user's input automtically
                td String
                td No 
                td ''
            tr 
                td exactMatch 
                td If enabled, wildcards will not be added automatically
                td Boolean
                td No
                td false
            tr 
                td autoClick 
                td When this is set to true and a search returns one result only, this result will automatically be clicked, triggering the given user event automatically
                td Boolean
                td No
                td false
