    h2 Events 
    p You can override the following functions in your code to adjust the default behavior.
    p 
        table.row-hovering
            tr 
                th Function 
                th Event 
                th Parameters 
            tr 
                td insertSearchDone(id)
                td Gets executed when the given UI elements of the search panel got added to the page
                td id = id of the parent div element (i.e. search)
            tr 
                td insertSearchDataDone(id, data) 
                td This function is invoked when the search results got returned and the tiles were added to the search result list.
                td 
                    ul 
                        li id = id of the parent div element (i.e. search)
                        li data = result data of the selected search as returned by the PLM REST API
            tr 
                td clickSearchResult(elemClicked, e) 
                td This function is invoked when a user clicks an item in the list of search results. It opens the given record in PLM per default.
                td elemClicked = jQuery element of the given tile which got clicked by the user; e = click event
